Patch to pytrainer 1.7.1 (which you get in the *buntu repository).  Replace '/usr/share/pyshared/pytrainer/extensions/googlemaps.py' with my version.

Google maps are still available using the dropdown selection on the map view.  This patch just replaces the base image with OSM.

Here are the differences:

140c140,144
< 		      mapTypeId: google.maps.MapTypeId.ROADMAP
---
>               mapTypeId: 'OSM',
>               mapTypeControlOptions: {
>                   mapTypeIds: ['OSM', google.maps.MapTypeId.ROADMAP],
>                   style: google.maps.MapTypeControlStyle.DROPDOWN_MENU
>               }
166a171,186
> 
>             // Use OSM data
>             var osmMapType = new google.maps.ImageMapType({
>                 getTileUrl: function(coord, zoom) {
>                     return "http://tile.openstreetmap.org/" +
>                     zoom + "/" + coord.x + "/" + coord.y + ".png";
>                 },
>                 tilesize: new google.maps.Size(256, 256),
>                 isPng: true,
>                 alt: "OpenStreetMap layer",
>                 name: "OpenStreetMap",
>                 maxZoom: 19
>             });
>             map.mapTypes.set('OSM',osmMapType);
>             map.setMapTypeId('OSM');
>             

(I think the current svn of pytrainer has OSM mind so perhaps not required?)

Free as in beer.
